 @steveliciousrex  um the 5090 uses a 512-bit, so right there is your change. by your knowledge that's like saying adding more cores to a CPU isn't going to add any performance jump. But oh how you are so wrong. A "512 bit bus rate" refers to a data transfer rate across a bus that is 512 bits wide, meaning it can transfer 512 bits of data simultaneously, which is typically used in high-performance graphics cards to achieve very high memory bandwidth; the exact speed depends on the clock speed of the bus, but a 512 bit bus generally indicates a very high data transfer rate. 
Memory bandwidth is key to high performance.

